On Dec 17, 2014 9:57 AM, "James Knott" <james.knott at rogers.com> wrote:
>
> Baudot???  I haven't seen that in
> decades!

It still lives on - in an admitted niche - in amateur radio teletype
digital modes. Because RTTY uses a very simple FSK coding scheme, it
survives amplification from nonlinear amplifiers quite well. It means you
get teeth-rattlingly loud signals blasting in from stations worldwide.
Usually all over your carefully crafted low power signal ... grar.

Stewart
