GTALUG operates under a code of conduct.  

http://gtalug.org/about/code-of-conduct/  

The code has some leeway it so that if certain kinds of comments or material appear, recognition and an apology are an absolutely perfect outcome (and this thread is a good example of that).

If anyone has feedback on the code, let me know.   I can always use more input.  Proposed revisions are reviewed annually by the board.

It's not good for the group if we ignore offensive comments.


